parameters: ...Huu ... \n< Serena >
Hey there. How was your day? Spread your legs wide,
would ya? \n< Watchman >
This will become a rumor again. \n< Watchman >
It doesn't matter. But let's remember the promise. \n< Serena >
Madam is quite the eccentric, isn't she? Doing
things like freeing caged birds on purpose... \n< Watchman >
I will not run away. I will definitely repay the
borrowed money. \n< Serena >
That's precisely why we're going to the guild. \n< Serena >
...Hey, now? After dancing all night? \n< Watchman >
No problem. But time is precious now. \n< Serena >
Well, I won't stop you. The door is unlocked. Just go
ahead and leave. \n< Watchman >
You know, you still have work to do at night. \n< Watchman >
No problem. \n< Serena >
Youth is so enviable. \n< Watchman >
Mmm...
\n< Serena >
Haa...I can't believe I let things get this bad... \n< Serena >
But today is the day of the promised deadline. \n< Serena >
The informant should be reporting some clues about
Splendor... \n< Serena >
I paid 250G and 25,000S for that. 5,000S were
borrowed. \n< Serena >
Thanks to the hard work, today it will all pay off.
Let's go to the guild and meet up with the informant. \n< Serena >
It's the building just south of here. \n< Serena >

events.name: 第二部ストーリー　シシリア

parameters: ストーリー　シシリア
Hey, your dance moves are really sharp today. I was
surprised when I heard you were going out overnight. \n< Deacon >
With that big belly, you can dance beautifully. \n< Deacon >
There's a constant flow of customers inquiring about
you. Perhaps I can understand why Madam is so fond of
you. \n< Deacon >
I can't really behave as freely as I would like to,
you know... \n< Serena >
I suppose it was convenient for them that I didn't
show up today. They were probably trying to make me
anxious and raise the price...or maybe not. \n< Serena >
Madam, you really know how to sweet talk. \n< Deacon >
Everything will be calculated. It was just right for
me not to show my face for a day. I will probably
raise the price by making them anxious... \n< Serena >
Hehe, yeah, maybe so. \n< Deacon >
Alright. That's the end of dancing for now. From the
next hour, please go out and entertain our guests. \n< Deacon >
Understood. I'll go right away. \n< Serena >
Oh? You're not disgusted? You usually make a face
like you've stepped in shit. \n< Deacon >
I'm also desperate. \n< Serena >
Oh, did getting kicked in the butt by the madam give
you some motivation? Not bad, not bad... \n< Deacon >
If that's the case, I'll have the next guest go
straight up to the second floor for the reception. Do
you understand what that means? \n< Deacon >
\n< Serena >
According to the madam, she says not to worry because
he is not a customer who does unreasonable things. \n< Deacon >
...As if I could be at ease... \n< Serena >
I understand. I can't refuse anyway... \n< Serena >
Hehe, nice. You've got a good look. Don't be so
gloomy - that's the face of a skilled prostitute who
knows how to flatter. \n< Deacon >
